Questions that arise after the accident: Are the stewards in the car illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long distance is forbidden
In the context of the tragic bus accident of the company Student Agency near Padua, Italy, the question arises whether stewards and passengers can travel inside the bus during the journey.
"If we wanted to strictly and formally comply with the law, the activity of a steward is contrary to the law on road traffic," said the spokesman of the Ministry of Transport Karel Hanzelka.
The accident in question, during which a 22-year-old hostess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck that crossed the bus path.
The girl was unfortunately sitting next to the driver in the most dangerous seat of the vehicle, although she had two other seats at her disposal.
However, the coach can have an accident, or even brake abruptly, even when the steward serves coffee or distributes newspapers.
What matters is whether the coach is under its technical data sheet equipped with standing seats or not.
If this equipment for standing seats is not approved, passengers must remain seated.
The Student Agency long-distance buses do not have standing seats; this has been confirmed to Aktu<0xC3><0xA1>ln<0xC4><0x9B>.cz by the director of the company Radim Jan<0xC4><0x8D>ura.
“This is a matter that we have dealt with with with the ministry and, at the beginning, it prohibits any movement of passengers.
Then they canceled it and we got the passengers to go to the toilet during the trip as long as they had their own seat," he said.
The law ignores the steward
"There is no unequivocal legal interpretation of the steward role - no legal prescription takes care of that role.
On the other hand, no legal requirement prohibits the carrier from offering services.
The law on road transport knows only the term of vehicle receiver; it does not define its rights and duties," adds spokesman Hanzelka with more ambiguity.
Josef Pokorn<0xC3><0xBD>, the director of the Department of Road Traffic, believes, on the contrary, that the law sufficiently deals with the problem.
"It all depends on whether the bus has permission in its approval to offer standing seats.
It’s all in there,” he said.
The coaches are divided into urban, where there are standing seats and limited maximum speed, intercity with standing seats and higher permitted speed, and long-distance coaches without standing with the highest permitted maximum speed and seats equipped with seat belts.
As in the plane, says an expert
Jaroslav Ho<0xC5><0x99><0xC3><0xAD>n, an expert at BESIP (Road Traffic Safety) in transport safety, does not see the movement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"During regular traffic, there is no danger. The situation can be compared to that of service in aircraft.
There, too, it is not certain when turbulence will occur and the hostess of the air can shake her head."
"But in the event that the coach braked abruptly, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
In the same way as in an urban bus or in a tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of stewards through internal regulations," he says and also believes that from the point of view of the law, the issue is not resolved.
Jan<0xC4><0x8D>ura is ready to remove these services
Student Agency is the only bus carrier to offer stewardship services.
He hires two hundred.
Even after this accident, the director does not consider their profession to be a risky profession.
“However, as soon as I get the impression that this is a risky profession, I will remove it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and newspaper upon boarding.
This would also reduce costs," he said.
The concern for safety is the reason given to the absence of stewards in his vehicles the director of the Asiana Alexei Litvine, which ensures, in comparison with SA, a very small number of lines.
"We don't have hostesses. We've been opposed to them since the beginning.
Sooner or later it will end in a fatal accident," he told T<0xC3><0xBD>den.cz a year ago.
A huge tragedy has happened
A young hostess from the Plze<0xC5><0x88> region, who had been working for the company for two years, died in the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably left the emergency stop strip without using a flashing light and blocked the way to the bus.
The driver of the latter tried to avoid it by means of a sudden maneuver, but he ran over it by his right side.
Jan<0xC4><0x8D>ura refuses that the two seats reserved for the stewards' rest have been sold.
"In the case of long-distance lines, it is not possible to book these places, they are blocked."
The company intends to file a complaint against the driver of the truck.
For the compensation of the girl's family, the agency will not wait for the court's judgment, but with regard to financial compensation, it also relies on the culprit.
An amendment to the law?
Not in sight
An amendment to the law, which has been in the works for more than a year, by a group of 30 experts from the Ministry of Transport, could provide details on the movements of the stewards on board the bus.
"But it has not reached any conclusion on this point.
In fact, she is not too interested in buses, but rather in the points system, the maximum speed on the highway and the use of the mobile phone at the wheel," says expert Hor<0xC3><0xAD>n.
"The Ministry of Transport does not consider the activity of stewards as something that would fundamentally endanger the safety of passengers," Hanzelka said, adding that the control of the safety of buses is under the control of the police and the office for safety at work.
