Brussels asked the Independent Scientific Committee to examine the problem, given the intensive use of portable music devices and the increase in the number of young people exposed to the noise they generate.
"Scientists-concludes the EU executive-confirm that there are good reasons to worry, and that the European Commission will now consider with Member States and other interested parties what measures could possibly be adopted to better protect children and adolescents, against exposure to noise from similar portable musical devices and devices.
